# Session Startup

At the start of every session:

1. Read `.claude/index.md` and scan for relevant knowledge entries
2. Read relevant `.claude/knowledge/` files (especially `project-architecture.md` and `todo-completion.md`)
3. List the `todo/` folder to find open TODO items (files not in `todo/done/`)
4. Read open TODO files in numeric order
5. Begin working on the lowest-numbered open TODO item
6. After completing a TODO, move its file to `todo/done/` and proceed to the next one

When completing a TODO:
- Verify the acceptance criteria are met
- Run `cargo check` and `cargo test` to confirm no regressions
- Move the TODO file to `todo/done/`
- Create a git commit summarizing the completed work
- Update `.claude/knowledge/` if the work produced notable findings
